column5: Just at work and the police told me that a tornado has touched down in York region.  Anybody up there see anything? Sitting at Toronto western and the skies looking pretty ugly.  Be safe Bill
No,just hearing some downed trees in Spring Water and Tiny townships.Looks like the Midland area had some high winds as well.
This was taken in Keswick about an hour or so ago.
possibility in keswick  the 2nd wave late this afternoon came through really fast and hard.
Thats right by the ice palace in keswick, i live in the south end and it missed us completely. I havent heard anything yet but i do know it got pretty hairy in the north end.
